<p><div class="msgquote"><div class="msgquotesrc">Quote:</div><div class="msgqorig">This post is just to rant at Sony for making it almost impossible to do. </div></div> <br /> <br />It's not almost impossible.  If it was, there would be a lot fewer paladins with it collecting dust in the bank. <br /> <br /><div class="msgquote"><div class="msgquotesrc">Quote:</div><div class="msgqorig">Even if I CAN for some reason gather enough people at any given time to raid one of the 2 dragons i'm supposed to raid... they are usually not up.</div></div> <br /> <br />There are more than just 2 that can drop it.  If you are talking Naggy and Vox, Talendor and Gore drop the books as well fairly regularly.  And I've seen a group of 3 take them both out. <br /> <br />I can understand your gripe.  I felt more or less the same way at one point(except for thinking you should be able to solo an epic). But I wouldn't count on it changing any time soon, since paladins have had the same complaints basically since Kunark came out 3 years ago. <br /> <br />And just think, with the new expansion, you'll have a new and improved epic that will be even harder to get. <br /> <br />I still think epics were a bad idea the first time around, and I doubt this time will be any better. <br /></p>
