<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>You make good points but - Depending on your server it is a fact that you can virtually NEVER find a dragon up.  Some of the Zek servers have a fairly low population I noticed, so players there or similar low pop servers could probably find a dragon up.  EQ was made for 1,500 players - in that general ballpark.  Fact is most of the more busy servers easily have 2,000+ on at any given time.  No sooner does a dragon spawn then, he is killed.  You made an interesting point too... it only takes 3 or so players to take out a dragon with modern gear, all the more reason why they are getting blown out of the water so soon after a spawn. <br />I don't know why you don't think epics was a good idea, I rather like it.  I did hear that with the new expansion there will be 15 or so different epic quests PER character.  I hope this is correct.  I can tell you one thing, I won't be happy if you have to have the old epic to start on the new ones! <br />My main point is that Sony should just take into account how many people are actually playing the game and decrease these crazy 3 to 7 day spawns on these quest mobs.  Does it make sense to you that Sony would allow only 2 people in 2 weeks to complete a part of their quest??  How fun do they think it is for somone to run all the way to the Emerald Jungle just to find that a dragon isn't up... for the 10th time that week.  It's not too fun.  It's also not fun to try to scrounge up a raid group when many people don't feel like helping somone, and would rather go about their own business- then find out that somone else killed the dragon in the 2 hours or so it takes to set up a decent size raid. <br /> <br />These mistakes could be solved so easily, it makes me wonder if anyone at Sony ever plays the game anymore, or if they are just too worried about EQ 2 to do anything about it.  I can tell you one thing, the existence of NO DROP and Anti-Twink Items make me angry too.  Who should say what I get to wear, or get to drop??  How realistic is it to say that I can't drop an item, and why shouldn't I be able to give my item to somone else?  Sony is pretty much braggging about how many restrictions on Powerlevling and Anti-Twink code they are putting in EQ 2.  Well I hope for their sake that most people don't think the way I do because i'm not even going to consider buying it unless they change their tune.</p>
