<p><div class="msgquote"><div class="msgquotesrc">Quote:</div><div class="msgqorig">I don't know why you don't think epics was a good idea, I rather like it.</div></div> <br /> <br />The reason I don't like epics is simple.  I've never seen any one concept in this game cause so much strife.  I've seen people quit in frustration at not being able to complete their epic.  I've seen guilds break up over epics.  I've seen just plain ruthless behavior in fighting over an epic mob.  I've seen good guild leaders and officers leave in frustration at guild hoppers who join just long enough to complete thier epic and join another guild that required it. <br /> <br />All that and more. <br /> <br /><div class="msgquote"><div class="msgquotesrc">Quote:</div><div class="msgqorig">Does it make sense to you that Sony would allow only 2 people in 2 weeks to complete a part of their quest?? </div></div> <br /> <br />Actually, it does.  The epic wasn't supposed to be a weapon obtainable by everyone.  It was made for the &quot;uber&quot; players of the time to have a long, involved quest for a great reward.  But everyone saw how sweet it was and wanted it too.  I don't think that Sony's vision of an epic was for a quest that any casual player could do.  And with epic 2.0, I'm pretty certain from what I've read that it will be the same concept.  You will only see these new epics on high end players. <br /> <br /> <br /><div class="msgquote"><div class="msgquotesrc">Quote:</div><div class="msgqorig">I can tell you one thing, the existence of NO DROP and Anti-Twink Items make me angry too. Who should say what I get to wear, or get to drop??</div></div> <br /> <br />I like them.  Sorry, but it took me three years to get my weapon from Ssar Temple.  And I wasn't one to be rolling in the plat or to pay RL money for in game items.  If someone else was running around with a Goldenrod on a level 12 paladin that they dropped a sick amount of plat to twink out an alt, it would irritate me.  I earned my no-drop items, and I have a degree of pride in the effort it took me to get those rewards. <br /> <br />But, I guess we just see it differently.  No worries. ;) <br /></p>
