<p><div class="msgquote"><div class="msgquotesrc">Quote:</div><div class="msgqorig">The reason I don't like epics is simple.  I've never seen any one concept in this game cause so much strife. I've seen people quit in frustration at not being able to complete their epic. I've seen guilds break up over epics. I've seen just plain ruthless behavior in fighting over an epic mob. I've seen good guild leaders and officers leave in frustration at guild hoppers who join just long enough to complete thier epic and join another guild that required it. </div></div>  <br />While I do like the idea of epics, this is a good point. People shouldn't let themselves get a fussy about getting the epic. There are other weapons out there of equal or greater value&gt; With the way the game has evolved over the year, they mostly have been regulated to status symbol, though some are still quite useful (read: cleric epic). <br /><div class="msgquote"><div class="msgquotesrc">Quote:</div><div class="msgqorig">I can tell you one thing, the existence of NO DROP and Anti-Twink Items make me angry too. Who should say what I get to wear, or get to drop?? </div></div>  <br />There are some very good reasons for this. One, it would be too easy to get the top weapons in the game. Uber guilds would farm them and then just sell them in the bazaar. Others would then just go out and farm plat all the time until they got the stuff they wanted. Also, plat dupers and the like would have even more influence on the game if lots of thing were no drop. Making things no drop it to encourage people to actually get off their rear ends and earn things the hard way, not just rack up as much cash as you want and by your way into time gear.  <br /><div class="msgquote"><div class="msgquotesrc">Quote:</div><div class="msgqorig">Sony is pretty much braggging about how many restrictions on Powerlevling and Anti-Twink code they are putting in EQ 2.</div></div> <br />Something I am looking very much forward to in EQ2. Then maybe I won't have top lvl warrior ask me where he has to go to learn taunt. (This happened to a guilde this weekend) <br /><div class="msgquote"><div class="msgquotesrc">Quote:</div><div class="msgqorig">Well I hope for their sake that most people don't think the way I do because i'm not even going to consider buying it unless they change their tune.</div></div> <br />Don't know about most, but I think the majority of players don't think the way you do. They are willing to go out and wait for the drops. That is part of the challenge of the game and makes people want to come back. Where is the fun in just waiting to buy something great or wait for a hand me down. </p>
