<p>If you have REALLY REALLY big cajones, are level 60 something, posess a Shammy made or Thurg Gate potion and have an AA horsey, you need noone to help you in Fear. <br /> <br />If you fit all the above criteria, go to the Fear zone in area in Feerott. Cast DA on yourself, and zone in. <br /> <br />QUICKLY summon your horsey. I have a hotkey for it. Just start riding around the zone training the mobs. Just like if you were a druid or Wizzy quad kiting. <br /> <br />Know where your NPC is. Run your train to the opposite end of the zone from him. Make sure you've trained EVERYTHING near him away. <br /> <br />You should have more than enough time to ride back, do your turn in and gate out. <br /> <br />I'm gonna do a dry run or 2 naked very soon. Don't wanna lose all my items/gear without a couple practice runs to get the timing down. <br /> <br />ONE IMPORTANT NOTE. You obviously do NOT want to do this should you zone in and find people hunting/raiding. <br /> <br />But if there's a raid in there, they might let you tag along and just maybe nobody's doing the Pally epic turn in. If they are, just gate out with your potion and try again another time. <br /> <br />After getting my Soulfire, I actually had decided the epic wasn't worth pursuing for various reasons some of you have posted. <br /> <br />But one night, the guild goes to Fear. For marsinger and other player's epic drops. Lo and behold, my BP drops. <br /> <br />We had to go to the Hole for a couple epics. Lo and behold some more, the Keeper was up. Got sword. <br /> <br />About a week later, a guildie sends me this tell that a couple guys killed Sev in EJ and that the torn burnt book was rotting. He held the corpse till I could get there (a Holy Steed is nice for lots of reasons)and I was able to loot it. <br /> <br />At this point, I decided it was fate. A group of us went to Nek after a server reset and ganked Kirak Vil. I wondered why of all NPC's that a DE should be involved. I now know. Whod'a thunk it. EQ's very own Darth Vader. <br /> <br />Sorry for rambling on. All that just to say that you can do the final turn in on your own. If you dare :) <br /> <br /></p>
