<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I did some testing of my Fear idea (which is partly borrowed, I'll gladly admit) the other night when our guild raided Fear. <br /> <br />Largely worked well for my first attempt. Zoned in with DA running, was max buffed, horsed up and started running in circles. <br /> <br />By the time DA and the Chanter's Rune wore off, I had a nice train chasing me. Our guild zoned in, got to the setup point and our Mage CoH'd me before I died. They grabbed a couple mobs because they zoned in a bit too quickly, but the theory tests out. <br /> <br />The hardest part will be getting to know mob placement between the zone in and the epic turn in NPC. But from just the preliminary trial, I should have plenty of time to train mobs away, do the turn in and gate out. <br /> <br />As far as raiding Fear goes, with a little practice, a Pally should be able to ensure a fairly trouble free zone break. <br /></p>
